================================================================================
What shinylaunchR distributes vs. what it merely runs
================================================================================
shinylaunchR is an Electron application that ORCHESTRATES the execution of R and
Shiny — it does not link against, embed, or modify R or Shiny source code. It
launches R as a separate operating-system process and communicates with the
resulting Shiny server over a local HTTP socket (127.0.0.1). This process
separation is the basis on which the MIT-licensed application remains clear of
the GPL copyleft that governs R and Shiny.

  Distributed in the installer (by this project):
    - shinylaunchR's own source/bundles (MIT)
    - Electron runtime (MIT) and its bundled Chromium/Node components
    - the native module keytar (MIT) and its dependencies (permissive — see
      THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md)
    - application icons (original work — the blue hexagon/play mark)

  Merely run or installed on the user's machine at runtime (NOT redistributed
  by this project):
    - R itself (see "R runtime" below)
    - Shiny and any R packages the user chooses to register/install — these are
      fetched and installed by the user's own R from CRAN/GitHub on the user's
      machine
    - any hosted/remote Shiny app URL the user adds

================================================================================
R runtime (GPL) — model actually implemented
================================================================================
R is licensed under the GNU General Public License (GPL-2 / GPL-3). Shiny is
licensed under GPL-3.

shinylaunchR DOES NOT redistribute R. The installer ships no copy of R. At
runtime the app either detects an existing R already installed on the user's
system, or (in the managed-runtime model configured in src/main/r-sources.json)
downloads an official R build from CRAN onto the user's own machine over HTTPS,
verified against a SHA-256 checksum. In both cases the user obtains R directly;
shinylaunchR is not the distributor of the GPL work, so no source-offer
obligation attaches to this project.

For transparency, R's license is the GNU GPL:
  https://www.r-project.org/Licenses/
  R sources (per version) are available from CRAN: https://cran.r-project.org/

Shiny and user-selected R packages are installed by the user's own R from CRAN
or GitHub at runtime and are likewise not redistributed by shinylaunchR. No GPL
copyleft therefore reaches shinylaunchR's MIT-licensed binary.

If a future build of shinylaunchR were to BUNDLE R into the installer, that build
would be distributing a GPL work and would have to include R's license text and
provide (or point to) the corresponding source for the shipped R version. This
build does not bundle R.

================================================================================
Fonts
================================================================================
The UI references "Inter" (SIL Open Font License 1.1) and "JetBrains Mono"
(SIL OFL 1.1) by font-family name, with system fallbacks. These font files are
NOT bundled in the installer — they are used only if already present on the
user's system, otherwise the listed system fallbacks apply. Because no font
files are distributed, no OFL redistribution notice is required. If fonts are
bundled in a future build, include their OFL license text under licenses/.

